Private '''Coron D. Evans''' (born 1844) was an [[United States|American]] soldier who fought in the [[American Civil War]]. Evans received the country's highest award for bravery during combat, the [[Medal of Honor]], for his action during the [[Battle of Sayler's Creek]] in Virginia on 6 April 1865. He was honored with the award on 3 May 1865.<ref name="History">{{Cite web |url=http://www.history.army.mil/moh/civilwar_af.html |title=Civil War (A-L) Medal of Honor Recipients |accessdate=17 November 2013}}</ref><ref name="Projects">{{Cite web |url=http://projects.militarytimes.com/citations-medals-awards/recipient.php?recipientid=532 |title=Coron D. Evans |accessdate=17 November 2013}}</ref>
==Biography== Evans was born in Jefferson County, Indiana in 1844. He enlisted into the 3rd Indiana Cavalry.
